Ques: Given list of Employee table. Find employee with 2nd highest salary ?
Ans: Optional<Employee> secondHighestSalaryEmployee =
                employees.stream()
                        .sorted(Comparator.comparing(Employee::getSalary).reversed())
                        .skip(1)
                        .findFirst();

        secondHighestSalaryEmployee.ifPresent(System.out::println);

Important Interview Follow-up

The above solution works, but if duplicate max salaries exist (Alice and David both have 7000), then skipping 1 may still return another employee with the same highest salary.

A better approach for 2nd distinct highest salary:

Optional<Double> secondHighestSalary =
        employees.stream()
                .map(Employee::getSalary)
                .distinct()
                .sorted(Comparator.reverseOrder())
                .skip(1)
                .findFirst();

secondHighestSalary.ifPresent(System.out::println);

If you want the employee(s) having the 2nd highest distinct salary:

Optional<Double> secondHighestSalary =
        employees.stream()
                .map(Employee::getSalary)
                .distinct()
                .sorted(Comparator.reverseOrder())
                .skip(1)
                .findFirst();

if (secondHighestSalary.isPresent()) {
    employees.stream()
            .filter(e -> e.getSalary() == secondHighestSalary.get())
            .forEach(System.out::println);
}

